HEADWORD: Swagbelly
<hw>Swag"bel`ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
prominent, overhanging belly.</def> <rj><au>Smollett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Any large tumor developed in the
abdomen, and neither fluctuating nor sonorous.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swage</ent>⟦br⟧
